<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="68" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="68">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="68">Addition to the original description. Males. Mesopleuron covered with sparse elongated punctures, almost polished towards metapleuron; without well-defined scrobal sulcus, but with enlarged fovea, more or less deeply excavated; metapleuron polished, transversally striate in upper part (Plate 5). Females. Punctuation on mesopleuron similar to the those of the males, with more aligned punctures; short scrobal sulcus, ending in a big and deep fovea; metapleuron entirely transversally striate (Plate 6).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="68">Variation. The specimen from Gansu with head and mesosoma metallic greenish-blue.</paragraph>
